@Node "TEXTUREPATH_GET" "TextureStudio.guide/TEXTUREPATH_GET"
@Next "TEXTURES_GET"
@Prev "SCREEN_FRONT"
@Toc "ARexx commands"

TEXTUREPATH_GET
---------------

@{i}Command@{ui}
     TEXTUREPATH_GET

@{i}Parameters template@{ui}
     None.

@{i}Return template@{ui}
     PATH

@{i}Description@{ui}
     This returns the user's current directory (path) for textures.

     This command is useful used in conjunction with FILE_JOIN, see
     @{"FILE_JOIN" Link "FILE_JOIN"}.

@{i}Parameters@{ui}
     None.

@{i}Returns@{ui}
    PATH
          The user's render path.

@{i}Errors@{ui}
     rc = 0 if the operation was successful.

     rc = 10 if the operation failed for any reason, rc2 will contain a
     string describing the problem.

@{i}Example@{ui}
     The following gets the user's texture path and returns it in a
     varaible called `pathpart'

          TEXTUREPATH_GET VAR 'pathpart'

@{i}Known bugs@{ui}
     None.


@EndNode

@Node "TEXTURES_GET" "TextureStudio.guide/TEXTURES_GET"
@Next "TEXTURE_SELECT"
@Prev "TEXTUREPATH_GET"
@Toc "ARexx commands"

TEXTURES_GET
------------

@{i}Command@{ui}
     TEXTURES_GET

@{i}Parameters template@{ui}
     None.

@{i}Return template@{ui}
     NAME/M

@{i}Description@{ui}
     This gets the names of all the currently open textures.

@{i}Parameters@{ui}
     None.

@{i}Returns@{ui}
    NAME/M
          The names of all the textures.

@{i}Errors@{ui}
     rc = 0 if the operation was successful.

     rc = 10 if the operation failed for any reason, rc2 will contain a
     string describing the problem.

@{i}Example@{ui}
     The following example gets the names of all the open textures and
     displays each one in turn with a requester.

          TEXTURES_GET STEM 'texture.'
          
          do l = 0 to (texture.name.count - 1)
             REQUEST_MESSAGE TEXT '"'texture.name.l'"',
                BUTTONTEXT '"More...|Cancel"' AUTOCANCEL
          end

@{i}Known bugs@{ui}
     None.


@EndNode

@Node "TEXTURE_SELECT" "TextureStudio.guide/TEXTURE_SELECT"
@Next "VIEW_GET"
@Prev "TEXTURES_GET"
@Toc "ARexx commands"

TEXTURE_SELECT
--------------

@{i}Command@{ui}
     TEXTURE_SELECT

@{i}Parameters template@{ui}
     NAME/A

@{i}Return template@{ui}
     None.

@{i}Description@{ui}
     Selects a texture to make it the current texture.

@{i}Parameters@{ui}
    NAME/A
          This is the name of texture. You need only supply as many
          characters in the name to distinguish it from other textures.
          For example, if you wanted to select the `GasGiant' texture,
          you need only give a NAME of `GasG'.

          The name is case insensitive.

@{i}Returns@{ui}
     Nothing.

@{i}Errors@{ui}
     rc = 0 if the operation was successful.

     rc = 10 if the operation failed for any reason, rc2 will contain a
     string describing the problem.

@{i}Example@{ui}
     The following example selects the `Radar' texture.

          TEXTURE_SELECT "Radar"

@{i}Known bugs@{ui}
     None.


@EndNode

@Node "VIEW_GET" "TextureStudio.guide/VIEW_GET"
@Next "VIEW_SET"
