     rc = 10 if the operation failed for any reason, rc2 will contain a
     string describing the problem.

@{i}Example@{ui}
     The following example gets the current view settings and returns
     them in a variable called `view.'

          VIEW_GET STEM 'view.'

@{i}Known bugs@{ui}
     None.

     See @{"VIEW_SET" Link "VIEW_SET"}.

     See @{"View window" Link "View window"}.


@EndNode

@Node "VIEW_SET" "TextureStudio.guide/VIEW_SET"
@Prev "VIEW_GET"
@Toc "ARexx commands"

VIEW_SET
--------

@{i}Command@{ui}
     VIEW_GET

@{i}Parameters template@{ui}
     VISIBLEWIDTH,XYASPECT

@{i}Return template@{ui}
     None.

@{i}Description@{ui}
     Sets the current view settings.

@{i}Parameters@{ui}
    VISIBLEWIDTH
          The current visible width as a floating point number.

    XYASPECT
          The current X/Y aspect ratio as a floating point number.

@{i}Returns@{ui}
     Nothing.

@{i}Errors@{ui}
     rc = 0 if the operation was successful.

     rc = 10 if the operation failed for any reason, rc2 will contain a
     string describing the problem.

@{i}Example@{ui}
     The following example sets the current visible width to be 50
     units and the aspect ratio to be 1.

